1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:02,335
[man 1] <i>Is it true?</i>

2
00:00:02,419 --> 00:00:03,920
[Usman] <i>Was Sir Marcus kidnapped?</i>

3
00:00:04,004 --> 00:00:05,338
[Espina] <i>We'll find him.</i>

4
00:00:05,422 --> 00:00:08,216
You seem pleased
with what happened to Reyes. Why?

5
00:00:08,299 --> 00:00:10,051
Nothing bad would happen to him.

6
00:00:10,135 --> 00:00:12,512
You know why?
Because weeds don't die easily.

7
00:00:13,638 --> 00:00:15,765
[in distorted voice]
What did Mustapha tell you?

8
00:00:15,849 --> 00:00:17,100
Show yourself!

9
00:00:17,183 --> 00:00:19,144
[in distorted voice]
Let's see how tough you are.

10
00:00:19,227 --> 00:00:20,812
- [electricity buzzing]
- [Marcus grunting]

11
00:00:22,272 --> 00:00:23,231
[dramatic sting]

12
00:00:23,314 --> 00:00:25,316
- [Jamilah] <i>Don't worry, Doctor.</i>
- [groans]

13
00:00:25,400 --> 00:00:30,780
I'm sure the TFA is doing
everything they can to find him.

14
00:00:30,864 --> 00:00:32,532
[Jamilah] <i>Especially Major Espina.</i>

15
00:00:32,615 --> 00:00:35,535
We need to know where they took Reyes.

16
00:00:35,618 --> 00:00:39,622
Don't worry. The TFA is already
on the ground to look for Marcus.

17
00:00:39,706 --> 00:00:41,791
Why is Sir Felix not here with us?

18
00:00:41,875 --> 00:00:43,209
He's at the S.Trinidad Hospital.

19
00:00:43,293 --> 00:00:44,961
He's assigned
to General Carillo's security.

20
00:00:45,044 --> 00:00:46,337
[Raquel] <i>What's going on?</i>

21
00:00:46,421 --> 00:00:48,089
- [Manuel] We're being ambushed!
- [rapid gunfire]

22
00:00:48,173 --> 00:00:49,090
‪[glass shatters]

23
00:00:49,174 --> 00:00:50,133
- [gunshots]
- [groans in pain]

24
00:00:50,216 --> 00:00:51,676
[Raquel] Hurry up! Hurry up!

25
00:00:51,760 --> 00:00:53,553
[in English] I'll take over.
Sorry for the confusion.

26
00:00:53,636 --> 00:00:55,096
[in English] Prep the OR!

27
00:00:55,180 --> 00:00:57,515
[Felix] <i>You, Jamilah Abubakar…</i>

28
00:00:58,308 --> 00:00:59,893
<i>You are the key to everything.</i>

29
00:00:59,976 --> 00:01:02,645
He wanted nothing but to protect you.

30
00:01:02,729 --> 00:01:05,231
[in English] And for that,
I will be forever grateful.

31
00:01:05,315 --> 00:01:07,525
[Nathalia] <i>Let me know</i>
<i>as soon as he wakes up.</i>

32
00:01:10,487 --> 00:01:12,197
[man] <i>Miss, this is</i>
<i>for Major Allan Espina.</i>

33
00:01:12,280 --> 00:01:13,114
<i>It's urgent.</i>

34
00:01:13,198 --> 00:01:15,658
Can I get your name? Who is it from?

35
00:01:16,409 --> 00:01:18,119
[young Gabriel] <i>Marcus, wake up!</i>

36
00:01:18,203 --> 00:01:21,539
Marcus, don't give up! You got this!

37
00:01:22,624 --> 00:01:25,043
[Espina] <i>Is it you, Madrigal?</i>
<i>Did you kidnap Reyes?</i>

38
00:01:25,627 --> 00:01:27,212
Where did you take him?

39
00:01:27,295 --> 00:01:30,006
Sir, this came for you.
It says here it's urgent.

40
00:01:30,089 --> 00:01:32,592
‪[music intensifies, concludes]

41
00:01:33,343 --> 00:01:39,015
[mysterious theme music playing]

42
00:01:50,235 --> 00:01:54,447
[ominous music playing]

43
00:02:01,412 --> 00:02:03,123
We received an intel earlier

44
00:02:03,206 --> 00:02:05,708
regarding Agent Reyes's whereabouts.

45
00:02:05,792 --> 00:02:08,044
Sir, how can we verify if that's accurate?

46
00:02:08,128 --> 00:02:09,462
Who did it come from, sir?

47
00:02:09,546 --> 00:02:11,381
Sir, we have no other lead for now.

48
00:02:11,464 --> 00:02:14,551
I understand your doubts,
that this could be a trap!

49
00:02:14,634 --> 00:02:16,136
I'm ready to risk it.

50
00:02:16,219 --> 00:02:17,846
Who's coming with me?

51
00:02:17,929 --> 00:02:18,847
I am.

52
00:02:18,930 --> 00:02:20,348
So am I, sir.

53
00:02:20,431 --> 00:02:22,308
- Me too.
- [in English] Co-- Count me in.

54
00:02:23,017 --> 00:02:24,727
For Sir Marcus's sake, I'll go.

55
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:27,147
For my brother.

56
00:02:28,523 --> 00:02:29,399
[agent] Wait.

57
00:02:29,482 --> 00:02:30,775
Where's Sir Felix?

58
00:02:31,860 --> 00:02:33,695
We have reason to believe

59
00:02:33,778 --> 00:02:37,407
that Domingo is working
with the syndicate.

60
00:02:37,490 --> 00:02:40,493
Domingo? As in, Sir Felix?

61
00:02:41,327 --> 00:02:42,704
That Felix?

62
00:02:42,787 --> 00:02:46,624
That's why from now on,
he can't find out our plans.

63
00:02:46,708 --> 00:02:48,918
And he shouldn't catch on. Understood?

64
00:02:51,462 --> 00:02:53,506
Felix, that bastard…

65
00:02:57,010 --> 00:02:58,928
[sighs] General.

66
00:02:59,804 --> 00:03:02,724
Seems like Reyes isn't gonna
open his mouth at all.

67
00:03:03,725 --> 00:03:04,976
He's stubborn.

68
00:03:05,059 --> 00:03:09,230
[suspenseful music playing]

69
00:03:22,619 --> 00:03:25,330
I don't want him to die yet,

70
00:03:25,413 --> 00:03:28,499
because if he does,
we won't be able to find out

71
00:03:28,583 --> 00:03:30,251
what Ahmad told him.

72
00:03:30,335 --> 00:03:34,464
As well as who were the people
who worked with Ahmad!

73
00:03:35,798 --> 00:03:37,592
[in English] We're in position.

74
00:03:40,345 --> 00:03:41,888
[guns cocking]

75
00:03:44,515 --> 00:03:46,142
What should we do about Reyes?

76
00:03:51,314 --> 00:03:53,024
Kill him.

77
00:03:53,107 --> 00:03:57,195
[music intensifies]

78
00:03:57,278 --> 00:03:58,112
‪[dramatic sting]

79
00:03:59,614 --> 00:04:00,448
‪[dramatic sting]

80
00:04:01,950 --> 00:04:02,784
‪[dramatic sting]

81
00:04:03,993 --> 00:04:04,827
‪[dramatic sting]

82
00:04:08,873 --> 00:04:10,166
[gun cocks]

83
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:13,878
[suspenseful music playing]

84
00:04:24,806 --> 00:04:28,059
[music intensifies]

85
00:04:34,857 --> 00:04:37,318
- [gunshots]
- [bullets zing]

86
00:04:37,402 --> 00:04:38,695
What happened?

87
00:04:38,778 --> 00:04:40,780
Sir, we're being ambushed by the TFA!

88
00:04:41,364 --> 00:04:43,408
[rapid gunfire]

89
00:04:45,868 --> 00:04:50,915
[tense music playing]

90
00:04:59,382 --> 00:05:01,092
[young Gabriel] <i>Marcus!</i>

91
00:05:01,175 --> 00:05:02,719
<i>Wake up, please!</i>

92
00:05:07,932 --> 00:05:10,935
[rapid gunfire]

93
00:05:14,897 --> 00:05:17,275
[young Gabriel] <i>Wake up, Marcus!</i>

94
00:05:21,738 --> 00:05:23,406
<i>Marcus!</i>

95
00:05:23,489 --> 00:05:25,199
<i>Wake up!</i>

96
00:05:35,293 --> 00:05:36,544
<i>Marcus!</i>

97
00:05:37,462 --> 00:05:39,047
<i>Hey, Marcus!</i>

98
00:05:41,215 --> 00:05:42,717
- [rapid gunfire]
- [man grunting]

99
00:05:45,011 --> 00:05:46,721
- [rapid gunfire]
- [man grunts]

100
00:05:47,555 --> 00:05:49,140
I won't let you catch me alive!

101
00:05:49,223 --> 00:05:50,975
[rapid gunfire]

102
00:05:51,059 --> 00:05:52,268
[groaning in pain]

103
00:05:54,062 --> 00:05:55,521
[young Gabriel] <i>Marcus!</i>

104
00:05:55,605 --> 00:06:01,110
[tense music playing]

105
00:06:17,168 --> 00:06:20,213
[somber music playing]

106
00:06:20,296 --> 00:06:23,299
Marcus, you're saved!

107
00:06:25,551 --> 00:06:26,719
Marcus!

108
00:06:26,803 --> 00:06:27,845
Marcus!

109
00:06:29,097 --> 00:06:30,681
Marcus!

110
00:06:30,765 --> 00:06:32,642
Bro… Bro, you're safe now.

111
00:06:32,725 --> 00:06:34,352
I got you.

112
00:06:41,359 --> 00:06:42,485
Gabriel…

113
00:06:42,568 --> 00:06:46,614
[somber music continues]

114
00:06:52,578 --> 00:06:53,913
[Usman] Brother…

115
00:06:53,996 --> 00:06:55,081
[Espina groans]

116
00:06:55,623 --> 00:06:59,836
[Espina grunting]

117
00:07:01,254 --> 00:07:02,421
[Espina grunts]

118
00:07:03,047 --> 00:07:04,048
[Marcus groans]

119
00:07:04,132 --> 00:07:08,719
[somber music playing]

120
00:07:08,803 --> 00:07:10,930
[Espina groaning]

121
00:07:11,013 --> 00:07:12,014
Come on, bro. [panting]

122
00:07:13,099 --> 00:07:14,058
[Espina groans]

123
00:07:15,143 --> 00:07:16,352
- [Marcus groaning]
- [Espina] Bro!

124
00:07:16,436 --> 00:07:18,104
[Espina] Bro!

125
00:07:18,187 --> 00:07:21,899
Bro… Bro, we're almost there. Come on!

126
00:07:21,983 --> 00:07:24,735
[panting] Let's go. Bro, let's go.

127
00:07:24,819 --> 00:07:29,198
[panicked breathing]

128
00:07:38,708 --> 00:07:44,839
[sentimental music playing]

129
00:07:49,343 --> 00:07:51,179
- [Gabriel] Marcus! [sobbing]
- [Marcus] Gabriel!

130
00:07:52,263 --> 00:07:54,682
[Gabriel] Marcus!

131
00:07:55,266 --> 00:07:58,186
- Gabriel, don't be scared. I got you.
- [Gabriel wailing]

132
00:07:58,936 --> 00:08:00,563
Marcus!

133
00:08:00,646 --> 00:08:02,565
[Marcus] Gabriel.

134
00:08:03,232 --> 00:08:08,571
[sentimental music continues]

135
00:08:13,868 --> 00:08:17,497
Gabriel, hold on! Just hold on to me!

136
00:08:17,580 --> 00:08:19,165
Marcus!

137
00:08:27,173 --> 00:08:28,257
[breathes shakily]

138
00:08:28,341 --> 00:08:30,134
[Usman] Espina, we have to go!

139
00:08:33,513 --> 00:08:34,972
[Usman] Buddy, let's go!

140
00:08:35,056 --> 00:08:40,102
[clicking, groaning]

141
00:08:57,537 --> 00:09:02,625
[suspenseful music playing]

142
00:09:08,631 --> 00:09:10,007
[Teresa] Marcus!

143
00:09:10,091 --> 00:09:11,133
- Marcus!
- [medic, in English] Patient, male,

144
00:09:11,217 --> 00:09:13,719
36, multiple visible wounds and bruises,

145
00:09:13,803 --> 00:09:15,012
- first aid administered.
- Peter!

146
00:09:15,096 --> 00:09:17,098
- [Jamilah] The bed just arrived!
- [Teresa] Hurry!

147
00:09:17,181 --> 00:09:18,516
Quick!

148
00:09:20,518 --> 00:09:21,978
[indistinct]

149
00:09:28,985 --> 00:09:30,528
[all, in English] One, two, three!

150
00:09:30,611 --> 00:09:31,821
[Espina grunts]

151
00:09:31,904 --> 00:09:33,322
[Teresa, in English]
Jamilah, please assist me!

152
00:09:33,406 --> 00:09:35,408
[in English] Uh, oxygen, Peter!

153
00:09:35,491 --> 00:09:36,909
[in English] IV fluids!

154
00:09:38,661 --> 00:09:40,037
[Espina] Bro…

155
00:10:05,563 --> 00:10:08,774
[phone ringing]

156
00:10:10,651 --> 00:10:11,652
Hello?

157
00:10:14,739 --> 00:10:15,823
Are you sure?

158
00:10:17,950 --> 00:10:24,248
[sentimental music playing]

159
00:10:24,332 --> 00:10:25,499
[Azuelo, in English] Everyone!

160
00:10:26,917 --> 00:10:29,712
I just got a call from the hospital.

161
00:10:30,421 --> 00:10:32,006
Agent Reyes

162
00:10:32,089 --> 00:10:33,924
is safe!

163
00:10:34,008 --> 00:10:37,720
[cheering, applauding]

164
00:10:37,803 --> 00:10:40,306
Sir, the TFA members have arrived.

165
00:10:41,098 --> 00:10:42,683
- Oh?
- Come on, let's go!

166
00:10:57,782 --> 00:11:01,619
Major General Leopoldo Ocampo!

167
00:11:04,497 --> 00:11:06,457
Have you no shame?

168
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:10,795
You're among those who ruin
this institution!

169
00:11:10,878 --> 00:11:16,342
- [dramatic sting]
- [tense music playing]

170
00:11:24,308 --> 00:11:28,979
[somber music playing]

171
00:11:39,990 --> 00:11:41,492
[Teresa sighs]

172
00:11:49,333 --> 00:11:51,210
Marcus.

173
00:11:51,293 --> 00:11:53,879
Why did you leave your brother
all by himself?

174
00:11:53,963 --> 00:11:55,965
Look, he scraped his knee.

175
00:11:57,007 --> 00:11:58,676
[young Teresa] <i>I'm sorry, sweetie.</i>

176
00:11:59,844 --> 00:12:01,470
I know you're having a hard time,

177
00:12:01,554 --> 00:12:04,306
and on top of that, I keep
bringing you along with me,

178
00:12:04,390 --> 00:12:05,641
but…

179
00:12:05,724 --> 00:12:08,602
I can't ask anyone
to look after you for me.

180
00:12:09,728 --> 00:12:13,607
That's why I trust you
to take care of your brother.

181
00:12:14,817 --> 00:12:17,278
Can you do that for me, my baby?

182
00:12:22,199 --> 00:12:23,325
Allan?

183
00:12:26,871 --> 00:12:28,622
Thank you for… [crying]

184
00:12:30,458 --> 00:12:33,586
keeping your promise to me.

185
00:12:36,088 --> 00:12:38,716
You brought my son back.

186
00:12:39,341 --> 00:12:40,593
[Espina] You're welcome, Doc.

187
00:12:42,636 --> 00:12:44,305
I'm glad that…

188
00:12:44,388 --> 00:12:46,223
my brother--

189
00:12:52,188 --> 00:12:54,148
that Marcus is safe.

190
00:12:57,610 --> 00:12:58,569
[sniffles]

191
00:12:58,652 --> 00:13:00,488
Thank you, son.

192
00:13:03,324 --> 00:13:04,492
[sniffling]

193
00:13:04,575 --> 00:13:06,494
Thank you so much, son.

194
00:13:07,453 --> 00:13:10,998
[emotional music playing]

195
00:13:20,382 --> 00:13:22,343
[sobs]

196
00:13:24,637 --> 00:13:27,640
[Teresa sniffling]

197
00:13:33,938 --> 00:13:36,774
[Teresa sobbing, sniffling]

198
00:13:43,739 --> 00:13:44,740
- [in English] What?
- [beeping]

199
00:13:47,826 --> 00:13:49,161
[in English] Okay.

200
00:13:49,245 --> 00:13:53,916
[ominous music playing]

201
00:13:53,999 --> 00:13:55,292
General…

202
00:13:55,376 --> 00:13:57,169
Don't tell me…

203
00:13:57,253 --> 00:13:59,380
Marcus escaped?!

204
00:14:00,381 --> 00:14:03,300
General, they captured General Ocampo too.

205
00:14:03,884 --> 00:14:06,345
- [screaming]
- [cup shatters]

206
00:14:07,221 --> 00:14:09,139
That Espina,

207
00:14:09,223 --> 00:14:12,476
together with Task Force Alpha!

208
00:14:12,977 --> 00:14:16,522
They're the ones who saved Marcus!

209
00:14:17,064 --> 00:14:20,568
[screaming]

210
00:14:24,947 --> 00:14:27,533
- [screaming]
- [plates, utensils clattering]

211
00:14:27,616 --> 00:14:29,410
[General Carillo wailing]

212
00:14:29,493 --> 00:14:30,870
General…

213
00:14:32,079 --> 00:14:35,416
[music swelling]

214
00:14:35,499 --> 00:14:37,167
[music fades]

215
00:14:37,251 --> 00:14:42,840
- [ECG machine beeping]
- [morose music playing]

216
00:14:42,923 --> 00:14:44,425
I'm sorry.

217
00:14:45,050 --> 00:14:47,094
We were late in rescuing you.

218
00:14:49,263 --> 00:14:50,681
[Usman] Yeah, buddy.

219
00:14:50,764 --> 00:14:52,933
The way you were taken was so precise.

220
00:14:53,017 --> 00:14:54,184
No trace at all.

221
00:14:54,268 --> 00:14:56,979
[breathing deeply]

222
00:14:57,062 --> 00:14:58,647
What matters is…

223
00:15:00,024 --> 00:15:01,150
I'm alive.

224
00:15:01,233 --> 00:15:04,028
[inhales, exhales deeply]

225
00:15:04,111 --> 00:15:05,946
And you found me quickly.

226
00:15:06,030 --> 00:15:07,948
[Marcus groans]

227
00:15:08,032 --> 00:15:10,200
I owe you my life.

228
00:15:12,202 --> 00:15:13,412
Thank you very much.

229
00:15:13,495 --> 00:15:15,247
[inhales deeply]

230
00:15:16,290 --> 00:15:17,833
[exhales deeply]

231
00:15:17,917 --> 00:15:20,628
[beeping continues]

232
00:15:20,711 --> 00:15:23,380
They say you captured General Ocampo.

233
00:15:24,965 --> 00:15:26,342
That's a big deal.

234
00:15:26,425 --> 00:15:27,676
[Usman] That's right.

235
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:29,803
General Carillo is bound to fall soon.

236
00:15:29,887 --> 00:15:31,764
[music becomes thrilling]

237
00:15:31,847 --> 00:15:34,808
What happened to General Ocampo
is just the beginning.

238
00:15:35,935 --> 00:15:39,521
One by one, we'll take down
General Carillo's henchmen,

239
00:15:39,605 --> 00:15:41,315
until he's stripped of all power.

240
00:15:43,359 --> 00:15:44,818
[knocking on door]

241
00:15:44,902 --> 00:15:45,945
Son?

242
00:15:46,028 --> 00:15:47,363
Doctor.

243
00:15:47,446 --> 00:15:49,114
- [door clicks shut]
- [exhales deeply]

244
00:15:49,198 --> 00:15:51,951
[gentle music playing]

245
00:15:52,034 --> 00:15:53,494
Ma…

246
00:15:58,165 --> 00:16:00,417
We… should leave you two alone.

247
00:16:02,378 --> 00:16:03,504
Buddy, Doctor.

248
00:16:03,587 --> 00:16:04,755
- We'll be outside.
- [door clicks open]

249
00:16:04,838 --> 00:16:05,923
Thanks.

250
00:16:09,635 --> 00:16:12,137
I know your life is always in danger,

251
00:16:12,221 --> 00:16:14,765
but I'm still not used to it.

252
00:16:14,848 --> 00:16:16,266
No. N-No…

253
00:16:16,350 --> 00:16:20,980
No, I'll never get used
to not worrying about you.

254
00:16:21,063 --> 00:16:21,939
[Marcus sighs]

255
00:16:23,691 --> 00:16:25,025
I'm so sorry, Ma.

256
00:16:25,109 --> 00:16:27,653
[breathes deeply]

257
00:16:27,736 --> 00:16:29,571
I made you worry again.

258
00:16:32,199 --> 00:16:34,576
But you have nothing to worry about, Ma.

259
00:16:36,328 --> 00:16:37,705
I've found a solution.

260
00:16:39,373 --> 00:16:43,419
Once I'm gone, Allan will be there…

261
00:16:43,919 --> 00:16:45,713
to take my place. [coughs]

262
00:16:45,796 --> 00:16:47,256
You're so silly!

263
00:16:47,339 --> 00:16:48,298
- [pained chuckling]
- [sighs, sniffles]

264
00:16:48,382 --> 00:16:51,301
Marcus Adrian Salazar Reyes!

265
00:16:52,052 --> 00:16:54,138
That's not a good joke!

266
00:16:55,305 --> 00:16:57,307
My full name, huh?

267
00:16:57,391 --> 00:16:58,934
[coughs]

268
00:16:59,018 --> 00:17:00,185
You're mad.

269
00:17:00,769 --> 00:17:02,563
It's your fault.

270
00:17:03,439 --> 00:17:06,775
Once a child is lost,
they can never be replaced.

271
00:17:06,859 --> 00:17:08,694
[crying]

272
00:17:08,777 --> 00:17:10,612
And a mother's heart remains whole,

273
00:17:10,696 --> 00:17:13,866
always devoted to her children.

274
00:17:13,949 --> 00:17:15,242
[sniffles]

275
00:17:15,325 --> 00:17:16,702
Relax, Ma.

276
00:17:16,785 --> 00:17:18,037
[inhales deeply]

277
00:17:18,120 --> 00:17:19,788
You're turning into a poet again.

278
00:17:19,872 --> 00:17:21,582
[both chuckle]

279
00:17:21,665 --> 00:17:23,333
You're unbelievable!

280
00:17:24,460 --> 00:17:26,128
- [coughs]
- [sniffles]

281
00:17:26,211 --> 00:17:27,337
- [groans]
- [smooches]

282
00:17:27,421 --> 00:17:28,255
- Ouch…
- Oh.

283
00:17:28,338 --> 00:17:30,549
[chuckles awkwardly]

284
00:17:31,216 --> 00:17:32,092
[sniffles]

285
00:17:34,053 --> 00:17:35,095
[Teresa sniffles]

286
00:17:35,179 --> 00:17:36,722
[gentle music continues]

287
00:17:36,805 --> 00:17:38,849
[traffic noise]

288
00:17:39,933 --> 00:17:42,102
[melancholic music playing]

289
00:17:49,318 --> 00:17:50,360
[sniffles]

290
00:17:51,236 --> 00:17:52,696
[sighs deeply]

291
00:17:54,490 --> 00:17:55,699
[exhales heavily]

292
00:17:56,450 --> 00:17:59,203
[breathes deeply]

293
00:17:59,286 --> 00:18:00,204
[sniffles]

294
00:18:04,750 --> 00:18:06,960
I forgot to give Marcus the toy back.

295
00:18:19,306 --> 00:18:21,141
[breath quivering]

296
00:18:29,983 --> 00:18:34,696
[tense music playing]

297
00:18:34,780 --> 00:18:36,406
[young Marcus] There, I fixed it.

298
00:18:36,490 --> 00:18:38,117
[young Gabriel] Yay!

299
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:39,076
My idol!

300
00:18:39,159 --> 00:18:41,578
You're so amazing, big bro!

301
00:18:41,662 --> 00:18:43,288
[in English] <i>I love you!</i>

302
00:18:43,372 --> 00:18:46,083
[Marcus] <i>I love you too, Gabriel.</i>

303
00:18:47,835 --> 00:18:48,919
[young Gabriel sobbing] <i>Brother!</i>

304
00:18:49,002 --> 00:18:50,129
[young Marcus] Gabriel?!

305
00:18:50,212 --> 00:18:51,588
Gabriel!

306
00:18:52,422 --> 00:18:53,841
- Brother!
- Gabriel!

307
00:18:55,926 --> 00:18:57,344
Gabriel.

308
00:18:57,427 --> 00:18:59,346
Gabriel, don't be scared.

309
00:18:59,429 --> 00:19:00,848
I'll protect you.

310
00:19:00,931 --> 00:19:02,516
Yes, brother.

311
00:19:02,599 --> 00:19:04,685
[Marcus] <i>Now come with me, Gabriel.</i>

312
00:19:05,477 --> 00:19:06,979
<i>Let's go, Gabriel.</i>

313
00:19:07,771 --> 00:19:09,857
- Gabriel, hold on!
- [thunder roaring]

314
00:19:09,940 --> 00:19:11,108
Just hold on to me!

315
00:19:11,191 --> 00:19:12,192
Marcus!

316
00:19:12,276 --> 00:19:13,777
- [Marcus] <i>Gabriel!</i>
- [Gabriel] <i>Marcus!</i>

317
00:19:13,861 --> 00:19:15,195
- Marcus!
- [Marcus] Don't let go, Gabriel!

318
00:19:15,279 --> 00:19:16,613
- Gabriel!
- [waves crash]

319
00:19:17,531 --> 00:19:19,241
[Teresa] <i>He's my youngest.</i>

320
00:19:19,992 --> 00:19:22,119
He's been missing for a long time.

321
00:19:23,662 --> 00:19:25,330
[in English] Thirty years now.

322
00:19:28,542 --> 00:19:31,128
Sometimes I wonder why
he was the one who disappeared.

323
00:19:32,754 --> 00:19:35,340
They should've taken me instead, you know?

324
00:19:35,424 --> 00:19:38,510
But I decided…

325
00:19:38,594 --> 00:19:41,096
that my life needs to have meaning,

326
00:19:42,639 --> 00:19:45,726
so that losing my brother
won't be in vain.

327
00:19:58,030 --> 00:19:59,448
[breathes sharply]

328
00:19:59,531 --> 00:20:01,742
[Jalil] <i>I'm Gabriel.</i>

329
00:20:04,036 --> 00:20:07,164
<i>I'm the doctor's missing son.</i>

330
00:20:07,247 --> 00:20:09,875
<i>Marcus and I are brothers.</i>

331
00:20:18,383 --> 00:20:20,302
[softly] I'm Gabriel.

332
00:20:20,385 --> 00:20:23,555
[dramatic music continues]

333
00:20:23,639 --> 00:20:25,724
I'm Gabriel.

334
00:20:30,270 --> 00:20:32,272
I'm Gabriel.

335
00:20:32,856 --> 00:20:34,399
[grunting]

336
00:20:39,905 --> 00:20:42,324
Little by little, this agency
is being cleansed.

337
00:20:42,407 --> 00:20:45,869
[thrilling music playing]

338
00:20:45,953 --> 00:20:47,079
Thank goodness.

339
00:20:48,664 --> 00:20:50,707
That's my dream as well.

340
00:20:52,042 --> 00:20:53,669
And what dream is that, sir?

341
00:20:54,503 --> 00:20:55,712
To become a general?

342
00:20:59,758 --> 00:21:00,801
No.

343
00:21:02,261 --> 00:21:05,722
To leave this agency free from corruption.

344
00:21:16,275 --> 00:21:17,651
[door clicks shut]

345
00:21:20,153 --> 00:21:21,571
[foot stomps]

346
00:21:26,326 --> 00:21:29,663
[thrilling music continues]

347
00:21:29,746 --> 00:21:31,999
I'm glad you're safe
and sound, Sir Marcus.

348
00:21:35,919 --> 00:21:38,297
[clears throat] I didn't know
about the operation.

349
00:21:44,052 --> 00:21:45,220
[thrilling music continues]

350
00:21:45,304 --> 00:21:49,099
Sir, it's a shame you didn't
bring me along.

351
00:21:49,599 --> 00:21:52,561
I could've joined in rescuing Sir Marcus.

352
00:21:53,645 --> 00:21:54,688
Well…

353
00:21:55,856 --> 00:21:58,150
aren't you assigned to General Carillo?

354
00:22:01,069 --> 00:22:02,029
Anyway,

355
00:22:03,572 --> 00:22:05,407
why are you here?

356
00:22:05,991 --> 00:22:07,117
[clicks tongue]

357
00:22:08,493 --> 00:22:10,245
The general is safe.

358
00:22:10,329 --> 00:22:12,331
He's been discharged from the hospital.

359
00:22:12,414 --> 00:22:15,667
[music becomes unsettling]

360
00:22:17,085 --> 00:22:18,420
[Felix smacks lips]

361
00:22:19,671 --> 00:22:22,174
I'll be on my way. [clears throat]

362
00:22:22,257 --> 00:22:23,258
Domingo.

363
00:22:25,802 --> 00:22:28,013
Thank you so much for your concern.

364
00:22:29,598 --> 00:22:31,058
But it's okay, even if…

365
00:22:31,141 --> 00:22:34,061
you weren't there to rescue me.

366
00:22:35,145 --> 00:22:36,730
I understand.

367
00:22:36,813 --> 00:22:40,817
[thrilling music continues]

368
00:22:47,616 --> 00:22:49,242
You're welcome.

369
00:22:51,286 --> 00:22:53,121
Well, uh…

370
00:22:54,790 --> 00:22:56,333
I'm going now.

371
00:22:56,416 --> 00:22:59,961
[tense music playing]

372
00:23:00,045 --> 00:23:01,213
[inhales deeply]

373
00:23:01,296 --> 00:23:02,881
[Marcus exhales deeply]

374
00:23:07,969 --> 00:23:09,179
[door clicks shut]

375
00:23:15,060 --> 00:23:19,940
[music intensifies]

376
00:23:41,419 --> 00:23:44,089
[Felix] <i>They're starting to suspect me.</i>

377
00:23:46,216 --> 00:23:50,053
<i>I need to take out my enemies</i>
<i>here one at a time.</i>

378
00:23:53,682 --> 00:23:56,101
Stop being stubborn!

379
00:23:56,184 --> 00:23:58,937
Tell me who your accomplices are!

380
00:23:59,020 --> 00:24:01,398
[in English] How dare you
talk to me like that?!

381
00:24:01,481 --> 00:24:03,441
I'm still your superior!

382
00:24:03,525 --> 00:24:04,943
[suspenseful music playing]

383
00:24:05,026 --> 00:24:06,194
Azuelo,

384
00:24:06,903 --> 00:24:11,158
you have a long way to go
before you reach my rank.

385
00:24:12,617 --> 00:24:14,995
[in English] So,
you better know your place!

386
00:24:17,205 --> 00:24:19,040
When you captured Agent Reyes,

387
00:24:19,124 --> 00:24:22,752
you demanded that he reveal
what he knew about Sir Mustapha.

388
00:24:22,836 --> 00:24:25,046
Are you an accomplice in his murder?!

389
00:24:25,130 --> 00:24:28,216
[suspenseful music continues]

390
00:24:28,300 --> 00:24:32,387
Again, I don't know
what you're talking about.

391
00:24:36,766 --> 00:24:39,060
- [music fading]
- [traffic noise]

392
00:24:48,278 --> 00:24:49,237
Uncle.

393
00:24:51,323 --> 00:24:52,657
Well?

394
00:24:52,741 --> 00:24:54,618
Are you ready to see Jalil?

395
00:24:55,702 --> 00:24:57,245
Father has made his decision.

396
00:24:57,329 --> 00:24:59,122
[somber music playing]

397
00:24:59,206 --> 00:25:00,916
To be honest, Omar,

398
00:25:01,499 --> 00:25:03,752
I'm scared to face Jalil.

399
00:25:04,669 --> 00:25:07,214
But he has the right to know the truth.

400
00:25:07,839 --> 00:25:09,132
You know, Rahman,

401
00:25:09,966 --> 00:25:12,510
you're one of the bravest people I know.

402
00:25:12,594 --> 00:25:14,554
But when it comes to children,

403
00:25:14,638 --> 00:25:18,058
even the bravest parents find
themselves overcome with fear.

404
00:25:19,809 --> 00:25:21,978
He might get mad at me.

405
00:25:22,771 --> 00:25:24,522
He could hate me.

406
00:25:24,606 --> 00:25:26,816
[inhales, exhales deeply]

407
00:25:26,900 --> 00:25:28,652
But I have to do this.

408
00:25:29,569 --> 00:25:32,364
Father, Jalil is a very kind person,

409
00:25:32,447 --> 00:25:34,574
and he loves you very much.

410
00:25:34,658 --> 00:25:37,953
I'm sure he'll understand why you did it.

411
00:25:38,870 --> 00:25:40,205
Let's go.

412
00:25:54,844 --> 00:26:01,059
[ominous music playing]

413
00:26:06,648 --> 00:26:07,857
[car door sliding open]

414
00:26:13,238 --> 00:26:16,866
[Felix] <i>Will the moment</i>
<i>I've been waiting for finally arrive?</i>

415
00:26:18,076 --> 00:26:21,663
<i>Will you finally take me</i>
<i>to Jalil Abubakar?</i>

416
00:26:21,746 --> 00:26:27,043
[sinister music playing]

417
00:26:31,256 --> 00:26:37,012
[music intensies]

418
00:26:41,975 --> 00:26:44,561
I'm going to expose the truth now!

419
00:26:44,644 --> 00:26:47,355
[Azuelo] <i>Who are your accomplices here?!</i>

420
00:26:47,439 --> 00:26:48,732
What are you planning?!

421
00:26:48,815 --> 00:26:53,903
[Manuel] The people behind
this destabilization plot

422
00:26:53,987 --> 00:26:56,781
are Datu Rahman…

423
00:26:58,408 --> 00:27:02,120
…and none other
than his son, Jalil Abubakar!

424
00:27:02,203 --> 00:27:04,289
Just when we thought we'd already won,

425
00:27:04,372 --> 00:27:05,790
this happened!

426
00:27:05,874 --> 00:27:08,752
A man like Ahman
cannot be easily replaced.

427
00:27:08,835 --> 00:27:10,920
[president] <i>I have pondered this</i>
<i>for a long time.</i>

428
00:27:11,004 --> 00:27:13,089
My new Chief of Staff…

429
00:27:14,382 --> 00:27:15,967
- Buddy!
- Reyes, where are you going?!

430
00:27:16,051 --> 00:27:18,094
[Marcus] <i>I need to talk to Datu Rahman.</i>

431
00:27:18,178 --> 00:27:19,554
<i>I'll find out the truth.</i>
